{"/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_chinooksalmon_ver03/data/sn84020662/00414185940/1948112201/0637.xml":{"full_text":"NORTHERN\nLIGHT POWER CO.\n\u201cBETTER LIGHT BETTER SIGHT\u201d\nG.-E. Mazda Lamps Refrigerators\nElectrical Appliances Washing Machines\nWiring Material\n_Phone MAIN 105\nG/crUcA orf\u00a3 ^^9\nGleam O\u2019 Gold\nCHRISTMAS CARDS\nNow Ready\u2014\nPERSONAL\nCHRISTMAS CARDS\nMake good on your\nlast year\u2019s Resolution\nto yourself.\nChoose your personal\nXmas Cards NOW\nwhile the best selec\ntion is available.\nNOME DRUG STORE\nEye Glasses\nRepaired\nOne Day Service or\nJ\nRepaired while you wait!\n\nLarge Stock of New Frames,\nTemples, Glass Cases, Lenses\nReading Glasses, Bi-Focals\n\nLENSES DUPLICATED\nALL MAIL ORDERS\nGIVEN PROMPT ATTENTION\n\n35 Years Experience\nAlaskan for 21 Years\nLocated in May's Hotel, B Street Entrance\nTHOMPSON\nBox 344 NOME, ALASKA\nPresident Ends\nVacation In South\nKEY WEST, Fla. </P>\u2014President\nTruman let it be known Saturday\nthrough one of his closest associ\nates that he believes his adminis\ntration can avert another depres\nsion.\nRepresentative Sam Rayburn,\nspeaker-to-be of the House, laid\nthe administration position on the\nline here before flying back to\nTexas and a specking engagement\na. Dallas.\n\u201cIf a major recession or depres\nsion should come\u2014which I do not\nexpect\u2014it will not be justified by\nour economic situation, but will be\nman-made,\u201d Rayburn told a news\nconference after emerging from\ntalks with the President at the\ntemporary \u201cWhitehouse\u201d here.\nThis jibed wi h Mr. Truman\u2019s\nposition in campaign talks in\nwhich he contended another de\npression could be avoided only by\ndemocratic victory because of his 1\nparty\u2019s position that the GOP j\nwould look after the rich and not i\nall classes of the economy.\nMr. Truman\u2019s vacation drew to a\nclose Saturday. He se out for the '1\nbeach again for a swim and a sun- j\nbath\u2014his daily routine since his\na. r;val two weeks ago.\nHe flew back to Washington\nyesterday for a heavy schedule of\nconferences highlighted oy his\nmeeting today with secretary of\nstate Marshall and roving ECA\namoassador Harriman. Tney will\nreview the threats to peace in Eu\nrope, China and elsewhere.\nI\nAlaska Mayors\nMake Resolutions i\nAt Convention\n\nSITKA, (yp)\u2014The two-day con\nvention of Southeastern Alaska\nmayors, ended here Saturday with\nthe selection of Ke chikan for next\nyear\u2019s convention city and the\nadoption of six resolutions.\nMayors and city clerks of Jun\neau, Ketchikan, Peter, burg, Doug\nlas, Wrangell, and Hoonah attend\ned the sessions.\nThe resolutions urged the next\nTerritorial legislature to pass the\nfollowing legislation:\n1. Enabling municipalities to\nlevy a sales tax.\n2. Permitting municipalities to\nlevy property taxes on land and\nimprovements outside the munici\npalities to levy property taxes on\nland and improvements outside the\nmunicipal boundaries.\n3. Amending the fuel tax to pro\nvide that monies collected be spent\nin approximately the same areas\nand in the same proportion as col\nlected.\n5. Reques'ing a review of the\nmercantile tax law to improve col\nlection and enforcement.\n6. Requesting consideration of a\ntax on fresh and frozen fish in the\nrevised mercantile tax on the same\nbasis as on canned or mild cured\nfish.\nFIND HOMES FOR\nDRAKE CHILDREN\nTemporary homes have been\nfound for the two children of Earl\nDrake, former cook at the North\nPole Bakery, who died suddenly\nlast month. Tommy is being carer!\nfor by Sgt. and Mrs. Sam Widner,\ni and Gladys by Mr. and Mrs. Lester\nBronson.\nTheir mother is in the sanatori-\num receiving treatment for tuber-\nculosis.\nNew York became a city of\n2,000.000 telephones in 1045.\n0\nNavy To Play\nSanta Claus\nSEATTLE, (&)\u2014'The navy will\ncarry Chris mas presents and sup\nplies to the threshold of Santa\nClaus\u201d own domain when the at\ntack cargo vessel Sussex sails to\nmorrow for Kodiak.\nThe vessel, commanded by Lt.\nCmdr. Edward F. Carl, with Lt.\nDayton A. Smith as cargo officer,\nwill carry Christmas presents and\nsupplies for naval personnel in Ko\ndiak. John Fagin, chief hospital\nman, will perform as San\"a Claus\nwhen the vessel arrives about De\ncember 1.\nThe Sussex already has made\none Christmas ship voyage north,\ncarrying presents and supplies to\nnaval installations in the Aleu\ntians.\nNat\u2019l Grange For\nOleo Tax Repeal\nPORTLAND, Me. (/P) The na\ntional grange concluded its nation\nal convention Saturday after with\ndrawing support of oleomargarine\n\u2018axes and endorsing compulsory\nSuchow \u201cVictory\u201d;\nFighting Continues\nNANKING, (/P)\u2014Although gov\nernment dispatches claim that the\nba'tle of Suchow is considered\nclosed and a \u201ccomplete victory\nfor nationalist forces, it is eviden!\nthat fighting is still in progress.\nIn fact the battle apparently is\ncontinuing on all flanks of the\nnor hern Kiangsu bastion and the\ndecisive action may be yet to be\nfought.\nGen. Ho Ying-Chin. national de\nfense minister, reporting to the ex\necutive Yuan \u2018legislature*, said\nstiff fighting still in continuing in\nthe vicinity of Nienchuang, 33\nmiles east of Suchow, where a ma\ntes shm /{tuaaej oojoj pa>j jof\nback. Ho said that government\ntroops south of Suchow, on tht\nline to Nanking, will be reinforced.\narbitration of strikes that menace\npublic welfare.\nThe farm organization's policy\nmolders voted after two hours de\nbate Friday night to supr>o\u00bb**\ngarine tax repeal \u201cif and when ef\nfective means are taken to prevent\ndeception in its sale in imitation\nof butter.\u2019\u2019\nPolar Liquor Store\nBLACK Phone Your\nOrders\nAlaska Airlines\n4 Scheduled trips a week: Monday, Wed\nnesday, Friday, Saturday. Nome, (Moses\nPoint Flag Stop), Unalakleet, McGrath.\n(Farewell Flag Stop), Anchorage. Alaska\nAirlines IS STEADILY INCREASING\nTHEIR SERVICE to the people of Nome,\nand the surrounding districts. We are\nproud of our dependable service, and in\ntend to maintain the BETTER SERVICE\nto Nome. Low freight rates and even\nlower rates on produce shipments will\nhelp everyone\u2014Merchants. Businessmen,\nand Housewives.\nMail service four times a week speeds\nyour correspondence.\nAlaska Airlines maintains a Shopping\nService too, for your convenience:\nTRAVEL, SHIP, THE DEPENDABLE\nTHE STARLINER ROUTE.\nOne carrier service from Anchorage to\nCandle, Deering and Kotzebue.","height":"27112","width":"20380"}}
